		// TODO: For each mesh in the model that's a "cabin window" that needs
		// to light up when the lights are toggled in-game, add an includedRenderer
		// entry here. Why this is needed: If you don't have any includedRenderer
		// lines, then by default, ModuleColorChanger will hog *all* the meshes on
		// the part.  That's bad, because it breaks the F11 thermal overlay (the
		// part won't show any highlights). Sure, the Squad stock parts have that
		// bug, but we can be better than that.  :-)  Also, making it properly
		// behaved here makes the part friendlier for adding IndicatorLights meshes
		// to it (without the includedRenderer lines, the ModuleColorChanger ends
		// up stomping all over the indicator lights, too.) For each entry, the
		// name of the includedRenderer is the mesh name in the model.
		includedRenderer = window
		includedRenderer = porthole
	}

